+# FruitClaw DVI And Audio Optimization Notes
+
+Date: 2026-07-04
+
+This is a backlog note for fixing DVI jitter, screen noise, and dropped frames
+while RTTTL tunes are playing on the Adafruit Fruit Jam RP2350 `esp-hosted`
+FruitClaw build.  These are investigation notes, not completed fixes.
+
+## Observed Behavior
+
+RTTTL playback works again, but playing tunes can cause visible DVI disturbance:
+
+- screen noise
+- jitter
+- dropped frames
+- unstable display while audio is active
+
+This should not be treated as normal.  Audio playback should be able to run
+without corrupting the HSTX DVI stream.
+
+## Current Known Build Shape
+
+Current live build references:
+
+```text
+nuttx/.config
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/configs/esp-hosted/defconfig
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/TRMNL_DVI_TIMING.md
+nuttx/Documentation/platforms/arm/rp23xx/boards/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/fruitclaw-dvi-rtttl-recovery.md
+```
+
+Known-good FruitClaw DVI profile:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_BOOT_AUTOSTART=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_FB_RGB565_320X240=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_OUTPUT_SCALING=1
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_PIXEL_CLOCK=25200000
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_SCANOUT_PSRAM=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_SINGLE_SCANOUT_INTERNAL=y
+```
+
+Known audio and DMA-related settings:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_PIO=1
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_PIO_SM=0
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_DATA=24
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_CLOCK=26
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_DATALEN=16
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_MAXINFLIGHT=16
+CONFIG_AUDIO_NUM_BUFFERS=2
+CONFIG_AUDIO_BUFFER_NUMBYTES=8192
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_SAMPLERATE=44100
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_VOLUME=85
+CONFIG_RP23XX_DMAC=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_SPI_DMA=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_PIO_USBHOST_DMA_CHANNEL=9
+CONFIG_SERIAL_TXDMA=y
+CONFIG_SERIAL_RXDMA=y
+```
+
+Other relevant devices/features in this profile:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_WS2812=y
+CONFIG_WS2812_NON_SPI_DRIVER=y
+CONFIG_WS2812_FREQUENCY=800000
+CONFIG_RP23XX_BOARD_HAS_WS2812=y
+```
+
+## Working Theory
+
+The HSTX DVI stream is hard real-time.  It needs predictable DMA and memory
+service at the pixel rate.  RTTTL playback adds audio synthesis, audio buffer
+refills, I2S/PIO/DMA activity, and audio-related interrupts.
+
+The visible display disturbance probably comes from one or more of these:
+
+- audio buffer refill bursts blocking DVI refresh/copy work
+- DMA contention between HSTX DVI, I2S, SPI, serial, or USB host
+- interrupt latency during RTTTL synthesis or audio driver work
+- framebuffer refresh/copy from PSRAM to internal scanout happening while audio
+  playback is active
+- too-small audio buffers causing frequent refill activity
+- RTTTL sample rate higher than needed for simple tunes
+- unrelated load such as SD writes, Wi-Fi, Telegram, MCP, NeoPixels, or logging
+  happening during playback
+
+The DVI recovery note already established that internal SRAM scanout is needed
+for this monitor.  That does not automatically eliminate all jitter if other
+work blocks DVI copy/refresh timing or competes for DMA/memory at bad moments.
+
+## Optimization Ideas To Validate
+
+### 1. Increase Audio Buffering
+
+Current audio buffers:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_AUDIO_NUM_BUFFERS=2
+CONFIG_AUDIO_BUFFER_NUMBYTES=8192
+```
+
+Hypothesis:
+
+Two buffers may cause frequent audio refill pressure.  More or larger buffers
+could make audio playback less bursty and give DVI more predictable timing.
+
+Possible tests:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_AUDIO_NUM_BUFFERS=4
+CONFIG_AUDIO_BUFFER_NUMBYTES=8192
+
+CONFIG_AUDIO_NUM_BUFFERS=4
+CONFIG_AUDIO_BUFFER_NUMBYTES=16384
+```
+
+Validation:
+
+- RTTTL still plays without underruns.
+- DVI noise is reduced or gone.
+- RAM usage remains acceptable.
+- MCP, Telegram, telnet, and NSH still work.
+
+### 2. Lower RTTTL Sample Rate
+
+Current RTTTL sample rate:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_SAMPLERATE=44100
+```
+
+Hypothesis:
+
+RTTTL tunes do not need 44.1 kHz quality.  A lower sample rate should reduce
+synthesis and transfer pressure.
+
+Possible tests:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_SAMPLERATE=22050
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_SAMPLERATE=16000
+```
+
+Validation:
+
+- Audio remains acceptable for alerts and tunes.
+- Screen noise decreases.
+- CPU and DMA pressure decrease.
+
+### 3. Avoid Framebuffer Refresh During Audio
+
+Hypothesis:
+
+If the framebuffer is static while RTTTL plays, FruitClaw should avoid
+unnecessary DVI framebuffer writes or refresh-copy work.  Static image playback
+does not need continuous app framebuffer updates.
+
+Ideas:
+
+- Add an audio-active flag that tells UI/tool code not to redraw while a tune is
+  playing.
+- Avoid `dvictrl pattern`, framebuffer tests, or LVGL redraws during RTTTL.
+- If practical, add a DVI ioctl or helper to defer nonessential updates during
+  audio playback.
+
+Validation:
+
+- `dvictrl info` counters before/after playback.
+- No increase in `missed`, `max_frame_gap`, or `dma_errors`.
+
+### 4. Prioritize DVI DMA/IRQ Over Audio
+
+Hypothesis:
+
+HSTX DVI should win over audio, SPI, serial, and USB host when timing conflicts
+occur.  Audio can tolerate buffering; DVI cannot tolerate missed scanout timing.
+
+Things to inspect:
+
+- DVI DMA channel priority and IRQ priority.
+- I2S DMA channel priority and IRQ priority.
+- SPI DMA priority.
+- Serial DMA priority.
+- PIO USB host DMA channel usage.
+
+Validation:
+
+- DVI remains stable while RTTTL plays.
+- Audio still plays without severe underrun.
+- USB host and serial do not regress badly.
+
+### 5. Pre-render Or Smooth RTTTL Generation
+
+Hypothesis:
+
+RTTTL synthesis may be too bursty when generating data during playback.  A
+pre-rendered or more evenly chunked path could reduce CPU timing spikes.
+
+Ideas:
+
+- Pre-render short tunes to a buffer before enabling playback.
+- Generate larger chunks less often if memory allows.
+- Generate smaller chunks on a dedicated cadence if that avoids long CPU bursts.
+- Add a FruitClaw `rtttl.play` path that uses a board-friendly playback mode
+  instead of the most generic command behavior.
+
+Validation:
+
+- Compare the generic `rtttl` command with FruitClaw tool playback.
+- Measure DVI counters and subjective display stability.
+
+### 6. Reduce Background Load During Audio Tests
+
+When testing DVI/audio coexistence, disable or avoid:
+
+- Wi-Fi throughput tests
+- Telegram polling stress
+- MCP tool storms
+- SD writes or directory scans
+- NeoPixel effects
+- LVGL redraw loops
+- verbose serial logging
+- USB host device probing
+
+Once the baseline is stable, reintroduce services one by one.
+
+### 7. Check NeoPixel Timing Interactions
+
+NeoPixels use timing-sensitive output.  If NeoPixel effects run while RTTTL and
+DVI are active, they may make timing problems worse.
+
+Test cases:
+
+```text
+DVI only
+DVI + RTTTL
+DVI + NeoPixel static color
+DVI + NeoPixel effect
+DVI + RTTTL + NeoPixel effect
+```
+
+Acceptance:
+
+- Static NeoPixel color should not disturb DVI.
+- Effects should not run if they destabilize DVI/audio.
+
+### 8. Add A FruitClaw "Display-Safe Audio Mode"
+
+Possible release behavior:
+
+- Before RTTTL playback, pause optional display updates and nonessential LED
+  effects.
+- Play the tune with conservative sample rate and larger buffers.
+- Resume normal updates after playback.
+- Keep watchdog/guard heartbeat alive.
+
+This would be acceptable for an operator agent because RTTTL is mostly for
+alerts, not high-fidelity continuous audio.
+
+## Suggested Test Matrix
+
+For each test build, record:
+
+```text
+Build date:
+UF2 sha256:
+DVI profile:
+DVI scanout mode:
+RTTTL sample rate:
+Audio buffers:
+I2S max in-flight:
+DMA/IRQ priority changes:
+FruitClaw services running:
+Tune used:
+dvictrl info before:
+dvictrl info after:
+Visible DVI noise:
+Dropped frames:
+Audio result:
+Notes:
+```
+
+Minimum useful commands:
+
+```sh
+dvictrl info
+rtttl -v 100 -r 44100 "tone:d=1,o=5,b=60:c"
+dvictrl info
+rtttl simpsons
+dvictrl info
+```
+
+Also test the lower sample-rate path:
+
+```sh
+rtttl -v 100 -r 22050 "tone:d=1,o=5,b=60:c"
+```
+
+Important `dvictrl info` fields to compare:
+
+```text
+frames
+errors
+refresh: copies
+refresh: missed
+timing: max_copy
+timing: max_frame_gap
+timing: dma_errors
+```
+
+## Acceptance Target
+
+For the FruitClaw operator build:
+
+- RTTTL tunes are audible.
+- DVI does not show visible noise or lose sync during RTTTL playback.
+- Occasional UI frame delay is acceptable.
+- HSTX scanout corruption is not acceptable.
+- Audio tuning must not regress the known-good `320x240` RGB565 DVI mode.
+- Fixes must preserve BOOTSEL/watchdog recovery while alpha testing continues.
+
