+# FruitClaw DVI and RTTTL Recovery Note
+
+Date: 2026-07-04
+
+This note records the known-good FruitClaw alpha fix for two regressions on the
+Adafruit Fruit Jam RP2350 `esp-hosted` profile:
+
+- DVI was black even though `/dev/fb0` existed.
+- RTTTL commands returned without an obvious error, but no sound came out.
+
+The working baseline is the FruitClaw operator build, not the TRMNL build:
+
+- Framebuffer: `320x240`, `RGB565`
+- Output timing: `640x480`, 1:1 centered/scaled by the HSTX DVI driver
+- Pixel clock: `25.2 MHz`
+- System clock: `252 MHz`
+- Audio output: `/dev/audio/pcm0` through the Fruit Jam TLV320DAC3100 path
+
+Do not use this note as proof that the TRMNL `800x480` 2 bpp profile is active.
+FruitClaw intentionally uses the safe color `320x240` operator profile.
+
+## Known-Good Artifact
+
+The image flashed and validated during this recovery was:
+
+```text
+/Users/fred/Documents/FruitClaw-rebuild/nuttx/nuttx.uf2
+sha256: 91a13a8f452046a90a428bb81962bfe633e8ccb371cbbeb0bfd6ca9dcfc52cdd
+NuttX uname timestamp: Jul  4 2026 07:26:55
+```
+
+Build size reported by the linker:
+
+```text
+FLASH: 1200456 B / 16 MB
+RAM:    224864 B / 512 KB
+```
+
+## DVI Fix
+
+The FruitClaw DVI profile should keep the application framebuffer in PSRAM, but
+use the internal SRAM single scanout buffer for the live HSTX DMA stream.  This
+was the important stability fix for the picky HDMI monitor.
+
+Required config in:
+
+```text
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/configs/esp-hosted/defconfig
+```
+
+Known-good DVI symbols:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_FB_RGB565_320X240=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_OUTPUT_SCALING=1
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_PIXEL_CLOCK=25200000
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_SCANOUT_PSRAM=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_SINGLE_SCANOUT_INTERNAL=y
+```
+
+Why this matters:
+
+- Full PSRAM scanout could leave this display black or unstable.
+- Internal SRAM scanout keeps the HSTX DMA stream stable.
+- The application framebuffer can still live in PSRAM.
+- The validated runtime showed `scanout: [0]=... sram=1`.
+
+Expected `dvictrl info` lines:
+
+```text
+video: 320x240 fmt=11 planes=1
+dvi: fb=320x240 output=640x480 scale=1 bpp=16 bytes=153600
+clock: sys=252000000 peri=252000000 hstx=126000000 target_pixel=25200000 actual_pixel=25200000 clkdiv=5
+scanout: framebuffer
+buffers: count=2 split=yes
+scanout: [0]=... sram=1
+dma_errors=0
+```
+
+Smoke test:
+
+```sh
+dvictrl info
+dvictrl pattern colorbars
+```
+
+If the screen is black again, first verify that
+`CONFIG_RP23XX_HSTX_DVI_SINGLE_SCANOUT_INTERNAL=y` survived the last config
+regeneration.
+
+## RTTTL Audio Fix
+
+Symptom:
+
+- `/dev/audio/pcm0` exists.
+- `/dev/i2schar0` exists.
+- `rtttl` accepts a tune and returns to the prompt.
+- No audible sound plays.
+
+Root cause:
+
+The Fruit Jam ESP32-C6 coprocessor reset line and the TLV320DAC3100 audio DAC
+reset line share the NINA reset GPIO.  Audio was initialized during board
+bring-up, then `board_fruitjam_esp_hosted_start()` could later start
+ESP-Hosted and toggle that shared reset line.  That reset erased the DAC register
+configuration while the NuttX audio device remained registered, so RTTTL looked
+alive but the external DAC was effectively unconfigured or muted.
+
+Source files involved:
+
+```text
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/src/rp23xx_fruitjam_audio.c
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350/src/rp23xx_bringup.c
+nuttx/drivers/wireless/esp_hosted.c
+nuttx/boards/arm/rp23xx/common/src/rp23xx_i2sdev.c
+```
+
+The fix was to add a Fruit Jam codec reinitialize hook in
+`rp23xx_fruitjam_audio.c`:
+
+```c
+int fruitjam_audio_codec_reinitialize(void)
+{
+  g_codec_initialized = false;
+  return board_i2sdev_codec_initialize(0);
+}
+```
+
+The first recovery fix called it after successful ESP-Hosted initialization in
+`board_fruitjam_esp_hosted_start()`:
+
+```c
+ret = fruitjam_esp_hosted_initialize();
+if (ret >= 0)
+  {
+    g_fruitjam_esp_hosted_started = true;
+    ret = fruitjam_audio_codec_reinitialize();
+    ...
+    ret = OK;
+  }
+```
+
+This forces the TLV320DAC3100 register script to run again after the shared
+ESP/DAC reset.
+
+## Shared Wi-Fi/Audio Reset Hardening
+
+Date: 2026-07-05
+
+The alpha build now treats ESP-hosted Wi-Fi reset and I2S codec recovery as one
+board-level hardware domain:
+
+- `fruitjam_esp_hosted_reset()` marks the audio codec state dirty whenever it
+  asserts the shared NINA reset line.
+- `board_fruitjam_esp_hosted_start()` refreshes the audio codec after
+  ESP-hosted initialization even if `wlan0` readiness later times out.
+- Repeated `board_fruitjam_esp_hosted_start()` calls repair audio if a later
+  ESP-hosted reset dirtied the codec state.
+- `board_fruitjam_shared_reset_recover()` is the public board helper for tools
+  that need a known-good shared reset state before touching audio or Wi-Fi.
+- `rtttl` calls `board_fruitjam_shared_reset_recover()` before opening
+  `/dev/audio/pcm0`, so manual NSH tests and FruitClaw `rtttl.play` tool calls
+  both use the same recovery path.
+
+This means a Wi-Fi reset should no longer leave the TLV320DAC3100 silently
+unconfigured, and an RTTTL test should not depend on the ESP-hosted wait-ready
+result as long as the codec can be reinitialized over I2C.
+
+If RTTTL fails through FruitClaw, inspect both fields in the tool result:
+
+```json
+{"status":65280,"exit_code":255}
+```
+
+`status` is the raw `system()` wait status; `exit_code` is the decoded child
+exit status.
+
+Known-good audio config:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S=y
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_DATA=24
+CONFIG_RP23XX_I2S_CLOCK=26
+CONFIG_AUDIO=y
+CONFIG_AUDIO_I2S=y
+CONFIG_AUDIO_I2SCHAR=y
+CONFIG_AUDIOUTILS_RTTTL_C=y
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL=y
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_DEVPATH="/dev/audio/pcm0"
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_SAMPLERATE=44100
+CONFIG_SYSTEM_RTTTL_VOLUME=85
+```
+
+Useful checks:
+
+```sh
+ls /dev
+i2c dev 0 0x18
+i2c get -a 0x18 -r 0x40
+rtttl -v 100 -r 44100 "tone:d=1,o=5,b=60:c"
+```
+
+For the recovered build, `i2c get -a 0x18 -r 0x40` returned `00`, and the
+single long `rtttl` tone was audible.
+
+If RTTTL is silent again:
+
+1. Confirm `/dev/audio/pcm0` exists.
+2. Confirm the DAC responds at I2C address `0x18`.
+3. Confirm the ESP-Hosted start path still calls
+   `fruitjam_audio_codec_reinitialize()`.
+4. Do not assume `/dev/audio/pcm0` means the external DAC is still configured.
+5. Run one RTTTL command at a time and wait for the NSH prompt before sending
+   another command.
+
+## BOOTSEL Guard Notes
+
+During alpha testing, BOOTSEL recovery guards may still be enabled:
+
+```text
+CONFIG_FRUITCLAW_GUARD_BOOTSEL_RECOVERY=y
+CONFIG_FRUITCLAW_MAX_UPTIME_GUARD_MS=600000
+```
+
+If the board lands in BOOTSEL with reboot parameter `0x46435347` (`FCSG`), that
+is the FruitClaw guard marker.  After a successful flash, a plain reboot can be
+enough to enter the app:
+
+```sh
+picotool reboot
+```
+
+For production, the long forced BOOTSEL timeout should be disabled or converted
+to reset-only behavior after the release is fully tested.
+
+## Rebuild And Flash
+
+Known-good local build command:
+
+```sh
+cd /Users/fred/Documents/FruitClaw-rebuild/nuttx
+PATH=$HOME/.local/nuttx-tools/kconfig-frontends/bin:$PATH make -j8
+```
+
+Enter BOOTSEL from serial if CDC is alive:
+
+```sh
+python3 - <<'PY'
+import serial, time
+ser = serial.Serial('/dev/cu.usbmodem01', 1200, timeout=0.2)
+ser.dtr = False
+ser.rts = False
+time.sleep(0.35)
+ser.close()
+PY
+```
+
+Flash:
+
+```sh
+picotool load -x nuttx.uf2
+```
+
+Post-flash checks:
+
+```sh
+uname -a
+dvictrl info
+dvictrl pattern colorbars
+i2c get -a 0x18 -r 0x40
+rtttl -v 100 -r 44100 "tone:d=1,o=5,b=60:c"
+```
+
+Expected outcome:
+
+- DVI shows color bars.
+- `dvictrl info` reports `actual_pixel=25200000` and internal SRAM scanout.
+- RTTTL produces an audible tone.
