+# Adafruit Fruit Jam RP2350 NXDoom
+
+This profile builds NXDoom against the existing Fruit Jam HSTX DVI
+framebuffer.
+
+Expected display device:
+
+- `/dev/fb0`
+- 320x240 framebuffer
+- RGB565, 16 bits per pixel
+- DVI/HSTX output at 640x480 with 2x output scaling
+
+Build from the NuttX tree with the sibling apps checkout:
+
+```sh
+./tools/configure.sh -E -m -a ../apps adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350:nxdoom
+make -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)
+```
+
+Flash only when the board is in BOOTSEL:
+
+```sh
+picotool info -a
+picotool load -x nuttx.uf2
+```
+
+The board bring-up creates `/data` as tmpfs and mounts the SD card at
+`/mnt/sd0`. For Doom, remount the SD card at `/data` before launching:
+
+```sh
+umount /data
+mount -t vfat /dev/mmcsd0 /data
+ls /data
+```
+
+Put a compatible IWAD such as `doom1.wad` at the root of the FAT-formatted SD
+card so it appears as:
+
+```text
+/data/doom1.wad
+```
+
+From NSH:
+
+```sh
+dvictrl info
+dvictrl start
+nxdoom
+```
+
+If IWAD autodetection fails, use:
+
+```sh
+nxdoom -iwad /data/doom1.wad
+```
+
+Keyboard input uses the existing USB HID keyboard aggregate device at
+`/dev/kbd0`.
