+# TRMNL Profile
+
+This profile builds a minimal Adafruit Fruit Jam RP2350 image for the native
+TRMNL display client.
+
+It enables:
+
+- `/dev/fb0` as 800x480 `FB_FMT_Y2`
+- native 800x480 tight DVI timing at 25.2 MHz
+- one internal SRAM HSTX scanout buffer for stable HDMI timing
+- PSRAM/user-heap storage for the application framebuffer and image buffers
+- ESP-Hosted `wlan0`
+- `wapi` and `renew` for Wi-Fi/DHCP boot
+- `trmnl` with HTTPS, cJSON, webclient, zlib, and PNG decoding
+- `dvictrl`, NSH over USB CDC, BOOTSEL touch recovery, and bootguard
+
+It intentionally leaves out FruitClaw, MCP, HTTPD, LVGL, Berry, games, USB host,
+telnet, FTP, audio demos, and NeoPixel tools.
+
+## Runtime Files
+
+The minimal profile is set up to avoid blocking on `/mnt/sd0` during boot,
+because a missing or stale SD mount can block status/fetch paths on this board.
+The TRMNL app chooses runtime storage in this order:
+
+```text
+/mnt/sd0/trmnl       if the SD mount parent exists
+/flash/trmnl        if a board flash filesystem is mounted there
+/data/trmnl/device.json
+/data/trmnl/wifi.conf
+```
+
+The `/data/trmnl` fallback is tmpfs-backed and useful for bring-up, but it does
+not survive reset. The app has `/flash/trmnl` support now; the remaining board
+work is to expose and mount a small RP2350 flash MTD filesystem at `/flash`.
+
+For a one-off bench UF2, the same values can be compiled into the local
+`.config` with `CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_DEFAULT_ID`,
+`CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_DEFAULT_TOKEN`, `CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_WIFI_DEFAULT_SSID`,
+and `CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_WIFI_DEFAULT_PSK`. Keep those symbols empty in
+community defconfigs.
+
+`device.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "TrmnlId": "AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF",
+  "TrmnlToken": "runtime-token",
+  "TrmnlApiUrl": "https://usetrmnl.com/api",
+  "ImageFormat": "png"
+}
+```
+
+`wifi.conf`:
+
+```text
+ssid=your-ssid
+password=your-password
+key_mgmt=3
+cipher=2
+```
+
+NSH provisioning commands:
+
+```sh
+trmnl storage
+trmnl set-device AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF your-token https://usetrmnl.com/api png
+trmnl set-wifi your-ssid your-password
+trmnl config
+```
+
+`trmnl config` reports whether the token is configured, but does not echo it.
+`trmnl set-wifi` writes `wifi.conf` without echoing the password back.
+
+HTTPS certificate verification is disabled in this bring-up profile with
+`CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_TLS_ALLOW_UNVERIFIED=y`; install roots and disable that
+setting for stricter deployments.
+
+## Boot Behavior
+
+The board rcS starts DVI with `dvictrl start`, then runs:
+
+```sh
+trmnl boot &
+```
+
+`trmnl boot` starts ESP-Hosted, configures Wi-Fi from runtime files or compiled
+local fallbacks, renews DHCP, and enters the TRMNL refresh loop. Wi-Fi bring-up
+is retried with `CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_BOOT_WIFI_RETRIES` and
+`CONFIG_SYSTEM_TRMNL_BOOT_WIFI_RETRY_DELAY` so rcS can start before ESP-hosted
+is fully ready. Each finite fetch/render pass is guarded by the Fruit Jam
+bootguard so failed image updates return to recovery instead of hanging
+forever.
+
+## Build
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```sh
+cd nuttx
+./tools/configure.sh -E -l -a ../apps adafruit-fruit-jam-rp2350:trmnl
+make -j8
+```
+
+The UF2 output is `nuttx/nuttx.uf2`.
